inn1.comm: Two slips in place. nice little outswinger, gentle pace and Dinesh leans forward, bat and pad close together and taps the ball to the off side
Dinesh leans well forward this time and off drives to mid-off
swings from middle and off towards off stump, Dinesh gets forward to play with an straight bat, back down the track
another one curving away ever so slightly and Dinesh eases it towards cover.
Bit of rubbish after four lovely outswingers. This one is short and wide and DK slaps it over to the point boundary.
back to the original programming and Dinesh pushes it out to covers.
short and wide and Vijay puts it out of its misery.. He goes back and across to cut it to the point boundary
And the captain pushes this wide down the leg side. Neither Vijay nor Taylor can reach it.
finally a straight delivery; pushed out to mid-on
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
in the channel outside off stump, cuts in a touch but not enough to warrant a shot
overpitched on legs, flicked away for a single
well outside off stump and left alone
lands on a length around middle and leg, cuts away towards middle, squeezed out to the off side .. Vijay was almost squared-up but managed to hold his balance in the end
Mpofu has been bowing very well here. So far. This time another outswinger on the off and middle, Vijay defends carefully
leans forward to push the ball leaving him in the air towards covers
lands outside off stump, left alone
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
around the off stump line, Vijay stays back to push it to covers
in the channel outside off stump, left alone
pushes this down the leg side and Taylor, the keeper, gets a hand on it
fullish, on the pads, rolls to the on side
short and wide again and Karthik cuts it away to the boundary. Only Mpofu has bowled really well so far.
shoves this way down the leg side and Taylor makes a half-stop
Hmmm ... What is going on out there? Another way ward wide down the leg side. Poor Taylor had no chance.
Oh well .. Another wide down the leg side. Taylor goes flying but he is just Clark Kent without the caper. Can't reach it
Oh ho, it's a no ball now! And also outside leg stump but Karthik flicks it away
Karthik goes for the flat-batted heave and top edges it to mid-on where Price takes the "Catch".
still from round the stumps, full pitched on the legs and Vijay flicks it through midwicket
finally something in the off-stump channel, run down to third man.
on the middle stump and Karthik works it to midwicket. The over ends. Finally.  True story.
Meanwhile Mpofu continues to bowl well. This one he gets it to come back in - he has been usually bowling outsiwngers - and this one hits the pad .. going down leg, though
on the middle stump line, pushed towards mid-on
good ball,. tilting in towards middle stump, a tentative Vijay edges it behind square-leg

Aaha! The first bouncer of the game arrives and Karthik didn't tackle it all that well. He was trying to get on to the front foot and then tries to go through with the pull shot but top edges it towards third man. oops no top edge but it flies off the helmet.
slips in a slower one now and Vijay pushes it back down the track
gets forward to defend back down the pitch
goes right back to work it to square-leg
tries to reverse paddle sweep with the back of the bat but misses as the ball slides down the leg side
another wide down the leg side ... hmm the virus
goes back to turn the ball on the pads to square-leg
plays the reverse paddle, with the back of the bat, makes contact but the ball rolls to short third man
works this to the leg side for a single
on the middle and leg, turned towards square-leg

turns towards middle, Vijay was in trouble, gets out of the jail by just about getting the bat in front of the pad at the last minute. It was as if he was expecting it to drift to the pads and then surprised by the turn..
short in length, bounces just outside off stump and it has been punched back to the bowler
stays back to clip it behind square-leg
bangs in a bouncer on the leg stump line and Vijay lets it fly past his left shoulder.
in the zone outside off stump, left alone
slower one on the off stump line, Vijay waits before turning it between midwicket and mid-on
the off cutter in the channel outside off, left alone for Taylor to collect
length delivery around the off stump and Karthik square drives it through cover point
Aargh .. yet another wide down the leg side.
gets forward to wrist it to backward square-leg fielder
goes back to punch this to the on side
goes back, clears the front foot and punches it to long-on
arm ball on the middle stump line, punched down to long-on
on the middle and leg, going down with the angle, clipped past midwicket
slows up the pace, tosses it on a length around middle, defended on the front foot
back of length, jumps up almost chest high, DK mistimes his punch to the off side
length delivery on the off stump line, pushed to the on side
The bouncer and Karthik goes for a lame pull shot. It appeared as if he was going to withdraw from the shot but goes through with a weak waft .. the ball flies over the blade
stays back to clip it past square-leg

Vijay is run out. Absolutely lazy effort from Vijay and smart work from Taylor. It was tapped  past square-leg .. Vijay had stepped out looking for the second run but gets back. Here is where the drama starts. The throw comes to the front of the stumps and Taylor collects and back flicks it to the stumps ...Vijay is so lazy out there .. he was so slow .. and lands his bat down and drags ever so slowly .. unbelievably lazy. And he is run out. Thank you come again ..
slips this down leg for yet another wide. What's going on?!
goes back to defend to the on side
turns this to the midwicket region

Kohli is run out. It was reverse paddled towards short third man and they decide to get across for the risky single. Chigumbura, who has had an awful time with the ball so far, fires in a lovely direct hit .. Kohli tried to dive back into the crease but couldn't beat the throw. Out without facing a ball. In street cricket, if you had owned the bat, you would have taken it and walked off in a huff!
turns this one to short midwicket
fuller, drifts in from round the stumps, lands on the leg and middle, Rohit brings his bat down to jab it to the off side

almost got his man there! It was the one that went with the arm on the middle stump line. Rohit didn't pick it .. the bat and pad gap looked yawningly inviting and he just about gets the bat down to edge the ball to the on side
goes right back to work it towards deep midwicket
goes right back to defend it back to the bowler
presses back to punch it to covers
just outside off stump, eased to short cover
shorter, outside off, mistimed towards covers
on the off stump line, fuller, on driven back to the bowler
goes back to flick it to backward square-leg
drags it short and Karthik pulls it over straightish midwicket for a single
goes back to work it to midwicket
leans forward to defend the ball on the off stump line
goes back to clip the arm ball to midwicket
on the middle and leg, turned straight to square-leg.
floater outside off, cut down to sweeper cover
Rohit gets off the mark with a cut to deep-point region
India are wobbling here. Utseya bowls another floater outside off which goes on straight and Karthik decides to go for the cut but gets the edge. Taylor does well to hold on to it.
from round the stumps, with a slip in place, on the off stump line, squeezed out to the on side
loverly ball.. it lands around off and middle and moves towards middle.. Raina was looking for the cut and manages to push the ball to point
goes back to work it behind square-leg
from round the stumps, on the off stump line, pushed back to the bowler. One slip in place
on the off stump line, full, Raina leans forward to off drive to long-off
on the off stump line, tapped to midwicket
stays back to punch the off break to straightish midwicket
on the leg and middle, tapped to backward square-leg
almost run out ... pushed towards covers, looks for a single, gets back in hurry
drifter outside off stump, pushed to cover point
on the back foot, eased down to long-on
leans forward to push it to the off side
outside off stump, eased through covers
just outside off stump, punched to covers
flighted on the off stump line, on driven to long-on
drives on the front foot to extra cover
on the middle stump line, defended to the on side
around the off stump line, eased to point
gets forward to push it back to the bowler
turns away from the off stump, cut away towards deep point
takes couple of steps down the track and works it to short fine-leg fielder
presses back to turn it past square-leg
taps this one away to the on side for a single
works it to square-leg for a single
leans forward to push the flighted delivery to the bowler
outside off stump, cut away for a single
just outside off stump, cut to point for a single
on the middle stump line, turned past square-leg
turns away from Raina who punches it to sweeper cover
around the off stump line and Rohit plays a compact forward defensive shot
gets forward to wrist this to short midwicket
turns to the middle and off and Rohit was in trouble there ... just about manages to jab it down the track
leans forward to on drive to long-on
tossed up ever so slowly, gently turned to the on side by Rohit
quicker, worked to midwicket
top spinner outside off, cut down to deep cover
turns away from Raina who waits on the back foot and punches ti to long-off
just outside off stump, pushed out to covers
straightens after landing on a length around off stump, carefully deflected to short midwicket
around off stump, pushed out to covers
on the middle stump line, defended on the front foot
lands short in length outside off and turns .. Raina edges the cut shot
flighted full on the middle, driven back to the bowler
Delicious hit over the off-side field.. Raina sashayed down the track, stayed outside the line and lifted it inside-out over the in-field to wide long-off boundary.
presses back to work it through midwicket
leg break turns in from outside off stump, pushed out to cover point
flighted leg break and Rohit is beaten in the flight .. he goes through with the off drive and hits it uppishly clear of the bowler
leans forward to defend to the off side
on the off and middle line, eased to long-on
good delivery.. turns from middle and leg line, defended to the off side
,b>almost holed out to long-off Again, Rohit was beaten in flight. He had gone down the track but the ball dipped on him. he went through with the lofted hit and it falls short of long-off
gets down the track and off drives to long-off
quicker, flatter, turning towards off stump, from round the stumps, pushed to point
drifts to the pads, tickled around the corner for a single
gets forward to punch it back to the bowler
moves down the track, takes it on the full and whips it to long-on
goes back to punch the flattish off break to covers
again that tendency to drive uppishly as he is late on the front foot. Again not quite upto the pitch of the ball but he drives through vacant mid-off region for a single to long-off
on the legs, worked past square-leg
lands on the leg stump line, turns, Rohit goes for the sweep and is hit on the pad
on the middle stump line, straightens, pushed out to the bowler
drifts towards the leg and middle, full, pushed towards non striker
on the leg stump line, squeezed past the diving short midwicket fielder
moves down the track and drives to long-on for a single
goes right back and tries to dab it to the on side for a single .. it rolls away
pushes this one back down the pitch
on the pads, clipped away for a easy single.
quicker, on the middle and leg, nudged to backward square-leg
goes down the track and whips it to deep midwicket
nice delivery, he slowed up the pace and turned it from the off stump line, rohit lunges out to push it to covers
gets off strike with an off drive to long-off
flighted outside off, driven to short cover
on the middle and off line, turns in, tapped to short midwicket
fuller and Raina manages to get a single this time, down to long-on
slides towards the leg and middle line, glanced to fine-leg region
tosses it above the eye line, Raina doesn't take the bait and pushes it towards long-off
flatter, on with the arm, turned to short midwicket

tough chance for Price Very tough. Rohit went down the track and lifted it uppishly towards the non striker .. Price lunged out but couldn't reach it properly .. it perhaps just brushed his fingers... and ran away towards straight boundary
goes back to work it to extra cover for a single
on the leg stump line, swept to short fine-leg
Raina brings up the fifty of the partnership with a lofted hit to wide long-on boundary. He rushed down the track and heaved it up and over
leans forward to drive to long-off
nice flighted leg break turning from the middle and leg line, pushed to coverss
aaha neat slider outside off, skids away from Raina who is beaten on the attempted late cut
gets forward to wrist this past square-leg
turns away from the off stump, pushed through covers for a single
leans forward to push it  back to the bowler
goes for the sweep shot and gets it on his pad
gets forward to on drive to long-on
goes for the sweep and gets a single
gets down the track and pushes to the off side of the pitch

almost caught at long-on but falls just short of the advancing fielder. AGain beaten in flight. Cremer has bowled really well to Rohit. The attempted lofted hit carries the ball almost to the long-on fielder
leans forward to defend it to the bowler
straightens outside off, cut to deep point
turns in from outside off, steered to point
leans forward to chip the flighted leg break inside out over covers ..
long hop ... pulled to cow corner and the long-on fielder rushes across to make a diving stop
length delivery on the middle stump line, deflected to short midwicket
back of length around off, punched to left of mid-on for a single .. tight run but he gets across
fuller, tad slower, driven through covers
banged in short, Rohit plays a weak pull shot down to fine-leg
length delivery on the middle stump line, punched to mid-off

The Indian captain is gone. He rushed down the track but was greeted by a bouncer outside off stump. He lunged out and tried to cut it over point but edged it to the keeper. He was off balance .. and had to reach out well away from the body.
leans forward to drive to covers
leans forward to defend to the on side
leans well forward to defend to the on side
comes forward to deflect it to square-leg
gets forward to on drive to long-on
leans forward to turn to midwicket
turned away to square-leg
goes back to punch it to covers
goes back to the on side for a single
tries to get down the track but can't reach the pitch of the ball,. pushes to midwicket
stays back to work it past square-leg
floated on the off stump line, defended to cover
turns in from the off, defended away
punches the off break to long-off
gets forward to tap it back to utseya
stretches forward to off drive for a single
on the middle stump line, tickled past square-leg
Rohit's luck continues. He went down the track and was beaten in flight for the third time at least. He miscues the attempted lofted shot but clears covers
eased down the ground for a single
quicker, skids from short of length, turned to midwicket
stays back and taps the ball to the on side
gets forward to on drive to long-on
full delivery, driven to long-on for a single
on the middle and off line, turned to midwicket
just outside off stump, cut away to deep point where Mpofu fumbles
on the middle, pushed back to the bowler
spins in towards middle, tapped to midwicket
turned wide of short midwicket for a single
drifts towards the pad, gently turned to square-leg
slips to the pads, worked to fine-leg region for couple of runs .. Chigumbura chases it down
almost caught and bowled. He tried to turn the leg break from outside off to the on side and got a leading edge .. Cremer dived forward but couldn't reach
turns it towards midwicket .. confusion about a single but Jadeja manages to get back in time
lands outside leg and goes down for a wide
flighted delivery outside leg stump and Jadeja tries to whip it past square-leg but edges it to point!
stays back to punch the short-of-length delivery to long-off
clips this leg break that turns in more than he anticipated to square-leg
angles away from the lefty who lets it go through to TAylor. Taibu is out due to an ankle injury
length delivery just outside off stump, steered to point
some width outside off and jadeja cuts it wide of third man
short in length, on the leg and middle, clipped past square-leg
pushed across Jadeja who watches it sail past him
in the zone outside off, run down to third man
moves forward to rotate the strike with a drive to long-on
A rare short delivery from Cremer today and Rohit puts it away to the midwicket boundary with a pull shot
gets this fuller and Rohit eases it to long-off
leans forward to play a forward defensive stroke
back of length outside off stump, pushed through cover point
nicely bowled delivery, dipped on Rohit who lunges out to punch it past the bowler ..
on the middle and off line, going on straight, pushed down to long-off
well-flighted delivery just outside off, defended to the on side
quicker, fuller, jadeja almost stumbles out but manages to whip it to wide long-on
flighted outside off, wristed to short midwicket
slightly short in length, Jadeja stays back to clip it to deep midwicket
just outside off stump, Rohit punches it to sweeper cover
Stop the press. Six. Whoa! A long hop and it was crying to be put away. And Rohit obliged with a pull
leans forward to push it to the on side
leans forward to work it to midwicket
swept away for a a single
on the middle stump line, pushed out to covers
leans forward to tap it to the on side
shout for lbw but hit outside the line of off stump. Rohit was trying for a sweep shot there but ...
takes couple of steps down the track and pushes it to long-on
just outside off stump, pushed to short cover
shorter in length, skids outside off, Jadeja stays beside the line and cuts it wide of backward point
couple of steps down the track and as is his wont, lifts it inside-out over covers
outside off stump, mistimes the drive to long-off
full and outside off, driven to covers
gets forward to squeeze this one through point for a single
drags it short and Rohit pounces on it  ... unfurls a pull shot to pick up a boundary
fuller, on the middle, turned wide of midwicket
quicker one, on the middle, punched to long-on
full one outside off stump, driven to covers
on the middle and leg, turned past square-leg
really full delivery outside off, jabbed out to the off side
Rohit gets his highest ODI score. He moves outside the crease and crashes the full delivery to extra cover boundary.
really full one, pushed out to cover
uppishly driven towards long-on for a single

lovely delivery ... he slowed it up and tossed it across. Jadeja was early through the sweep shot and is beaten .. Price has a mocking appeal .. jumps up and down .. Quite a character this bloke .. I remember an earlier series .. his follow through was longer than a fast bowler's .. he was almost finishing up near the batsman on occasions .. glaring hard!
Rohit backs outside leg , Mpofu follows him with a full delivery, whipped to deep midwicket
Thwack. Length delivery around off stump and Jadeja punches the slower one over mid-off
low full toss, driven down to Coventry at long-on
Bosh! Rohit moved outside leg and Mpofu tried to follow him with a short delivery but ended up slipping it wide .. Rohit steadied himself and pulled it over long-leg
Nice shot. Again, he moved outside leg. Mpofu served up a full delivery on the middle. Rohit held his balance and square drove it to the point boundary
moves down the track and drives the low full toss to long-off
backs away from the leg stump and drives uppishly towards long-off
drags the full delivery from outside off to deep midwicket
on driven to long-on for a single .. Price is try8ing his best to bowl it really full here
And just as I type that .. he drags this one very very short .. easily pulled away
turns towards off stump, dabbed towards short third man
full, almost at the blockhole, driven down to long-on
full pitched on the middle, whipped down to long-on. Rohit gets on strike
Tonked! Nice juicy full toss and Rohit hammers it over midwicket boundary into the woods! Crunch!
lands short of the blockhole, driven to covers
fullish, on the middle, Rohit gets to the leg side and square drives but is unable to time it as well as he would want
Missed opportunity: It was a slower one and Jadeja edges his hoick between long-on and the straightish midwicket. Both fielders converge (coventry ran in from long-on)  and leave it for the other ..
misses to connect with another slog and Taylor fails to collect
quick and short in length as Jadeja moves down the track. In the end, he dabs it to midwicket
stays at his original position and swings this one to the square-leg boundary.
low dipping full toss, driven to long-on
Maiden hundred for Rohit. He is obviously all smiles. Cheers from the sparse crowd. It was a full toss around off stump and Rohit times it over cover boundary. Very nonchalantly done. Pure timing.
stays back to work this one past square-leg
gets down on his knee to sweep it to backward square-leg boundary
short in length and outside off, carved away to sweeper cover .. Ervine fumbles ..
length delivery on the leg stump line, worked wide of midwicket for a single
full delivery around off stump line, driven slightly wide of long-off fielder and they push for the second run
High full toss, above waist-high or so it appears on first look, just outside off, Rohit backs away, opens his bat-face and glides it through vacant slip region...

Rohit tries to slog a length delivery from outside off over midwicket but gets the top edge .. Taylor moves to his left and takes a tumbling catch. Rohit started off slowly but finished strongly to end up on 114. His first ODI ton.
in the zone outside off, dabbed to right of backward point
gets down the track but mistimes the drive back down the pitch
full delivery, swung to wide long-on .. Blignaut nearly over ran but manages to lunge back and stop it one-handed
Yusuf hits his first ball for a six over long-on. He bashed the full delivery from outside off over the boundary line ..
Smack! Again floated outside off and Yusuf blasts this one over covers.
drags back the length this time, punched away to deep cover
really full, turned wide of midwicket for a single to bring up his fifty. He accepts the cheers from the dressing room.
full in length and outside off stump, Jadeja slices it over covers
Whack. Full pitched delivery, Jadeja clears the front foot and lifts it to the straight boundary
Smashed. gentle back-of-length delivery and Jadeja pulls it to the midwicket boundary.
from round the stumps now, full delivery, driven to long-on for a single.
Ah! The bouncer arrives and Yusuf lets it go through to the keeper! He was shaping for the big hit and got that bouncer which he allowed to pass him!
And another bouncer. Yusuf tries to pull but can't get wood on leather. India finish on 285.

inn2.comm: Head band. He kisses the ball at the start of the run up. Off he runs for his first ODI ball. Fullish, around off and middle, hint of away movement, defended on the front foot
leans forward to push the full delivery to mid-on
length delivery just outside off stump, pushed to point. Two slips in place.
back of length and outside off, mistimes his cut to point
length delivery outside off stump, dabbed wide of backward point for a single.
Nicely done. It was full in length and tilting in towards middle and leg line and Taylor unfurled a neat on drive through wide midwicket. Wristy. Stylish.
length delivery that straightens on the middle stump line, moves past the poke and rolls away to the off side. Vinay too making his debut
pushes the length delivery towards mid-on and rushes for a single
climbs from short of length, straightens outside off, Taylor tries to run it past the second slip but makes no contact
in the channel outside off and Taylor shoulders arms
banged in short, Taylor hops back, taps the ball close on the off side and sets off for a single. Vinay rushes after the ball and Masakadza sends Taylor back
short in length and some width outside off, cut away wide of Amit Mishra at third man
length delivery on the off and middle, squeezed past square-leg
slightly away from the off stump and Taylor chases it but can't get a touch
full in length, just outside off stump, pushed out to covers
presses back to punch a back-of-length delivery to extra cover
bouncer outside off stump and Karthik collects
Swat-slap! It was slightly short in length and Masa plays a plucky little swat-pull over midwicket
length delivery straightening outside off and Taylor goes back and across to defend
presses back again and steers it to point
stays back to punch to left of Vijay at mid-off for a single
fuller in length and Masakadza leans across to punch it on the up and through extra cover
short in length outside off, mistimes the shot to the off side
Crunched! Short in length and some width on offer as well and Masakadza knives it on the up through covers
ooh good length delivery that held its line outside off, Taylor pushed inside the line and the ball flies past the edge
Very nicely done. It was a full length delivery on middle and Taylor flicked it past square-leg. ala Kallis
just outside off stump, shapes in, defended on the front foot
short in length around off, punched to mid-off
slower one, full toss outside off from back of the hand, Masakadza tries to adjust and has a big swing at it but fails to connect
full delivery around off, driven to mid-off
Another debutant. Full in length around off stump line, pushed back to the bowler.
lands on a length outside off and cuts away, Taylor goes back to defend and it runs of the outer edge to third man
hurls across a bouncer on the middle Masa is cramped for room and edges the pull to short fine-leg region. Karthik, the keeper, rushes after it but has no chance
another bouncer this time but slower and not too short and Taylor plays an imperious pull from outside off to square-leg boundary
follows it up with a good yorker and Taylor loses his balance but manages to dig it out to the on side
length delivery on the middle and off, pushed back to the bowler.
back of length outside off stump, punched through covers .. neatly done
short in length outside off stump, punched to the off side
banged in short and Masakadaza doesn't connect well with his pull but clears midwicket comfortably
around the off stump line. punnched to left of short cover where Yusuf makes a tumbling stop
wrists this back-of-length delivery from around off past square-leg
leans forward to defend the length delivery to mid-off
around off and middle, turned to Jadeja at square-leg
mistimes the pull to Jadeja on the leg side
gets forward to on drive and Rohit Sharma moving to his left from midwicket misf fields
Whack! It was a short of length delivery on the leg stump line and Masakadza plays a bottom-hand powered pull shot over the boundary. He sort of helped it along. Nicely done
length delivery on the middle stump line, defended to the on side
it kicks up from short of length outside off and straightens as well. Masakadza is surprised at the extra bounce from a back of length and is beaten, trying to push out at it

run out chance. Dinda misses. It was pushed to the on side .and they rush across.. the throw came in to Dinda who tried to grab the ball but spilled it! He breaks the stumps without the ball in his hands. The batsman was outside the crease but eh that doesn't matter now
gets forward to push this one for a single
Absolutely walloped! Masakadza moved outside leg and smoked the full delivery through extra cover.
slower one outside off, pushed to point
fullish outside off, mistimes the off drive to mid-off
short pitched stuff, swatted past square-leg
full in length just outside off stump, defended on the front foot
Imperious! Vinay shortens the length and that has disappeared over midwicket boundary. Crunchy pull.
short in length outside off, pushed to the off side
length delivery outside off stump, pushed out to covers
Smashed! He thrust his front foot forward, fetched the length delivery from outside off and blasted it over long-on
Crack! Short in length and well outside off, Taylor cuts it to the point boundary.
starts off with a delivery that drifts to the pads, the batsman goes back to clip it through midwicket
on the off and middle line this time and Taylor leans forward to defend. One slip in
presses well back to push this leg break to the on side
full, around off and middle, eased towards long-off
again very full in length, driven to long-off
on a length this time and pushed back to the bowler
on the middle and leg, turned to short midwicket
Fab hit. He rushed down the track, reached the pitch of the delivery and drove it hard past the bowler to the straight boundary.
from a slightly round-armish action this time, skids the ball in towards middle, punched down to long-on
on the middle and leg, turned to backward square-leg
on the pads, rolls away to fine-leg region for couple of runs
on the middle stump line, punched down to long-on
full delivery on the off and middle line, masa goes for the reverse sweep, misses and is hit on the boot.. Loud shout from Amit, Tiffin turns it down
leans across to push it to cover point
turns away from Masakadza who cuts to backward point
turns from the middle and leg line, tapped to the on side
skids outside off stump, Masakadaza goes for the cut and the ball flies through well wide of short third man.. He leaned back to cut it late

Done in by the slider.. It landed on the middle and off line and skidded towards the middle stump line. Masakadza tried to punch it through the off side, off the back foot, but couldn't' connect as he was beaten by the in ward movement. The ball skidded through the bat and pad gap.
leans forward to defend to the point region
arm ball comes in from the off stump line, defended of the back foot
stsays back to punch it to long-on
leans forward to defend
on the pads, rolls away to backward square-leg
stays back to clip it past square-leg
on the leg and middle line, dabbed to the on side
leans forward to push the leg break to mid-on
lands it on a length, driven back to Amit Mishra who fires a direct hit at the striker's end. The batsman is home
from wide of the crease, slides to the pads, rolls away to short fine-leg region
outside off stump, squeezed to the off side
slows up the pace, on the middle and off line, driven to long-off
around the off stump line, pushed to covers
flatter, quicker, around off, driven to covers
on the middle and leg, clipped to right of midwicket where Virat makes a diving stop
gets forward and this time drives to left of Virat for a single
